// Orchicon RecoveryService (docs/07_API_Specification.md §3.6,
// docs/06_Recovery_Workflow_Engine.md).
//
// Recovery workflow management: trigger/cancel, streaming events, and
// continuation-plan approval (docs/06 §8). The RecoveryReconciler
// progresses RecoveryExecutions through the default 6-step workflow
// (capture → summarize → preserve → review → plan → resume) and handles
// escalation (L1 → L2 → L3) and bounded auto-relax (docs/06 §11).
//
// MarkTaskSucceeded allows the Reviewer Worker (during recovery) or a
// human to mark a Task succeeded (docs/06 §11, docs/02 §4 #2). All three
// completion paths (Policy, Reviewer, human) produce an audit event with
// the actor recorded.

